Dorothy Lee (actress) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dorothy_Lee_(actress) 0 Dorothy Lee (born Marjorie Elizabeth Millsap, May 23, 1911 – June 24, 1999) was an American actress and comedian during the 1930s. She appeared in 28 films, usually appearing alongside the Wheeler Woolsey comedy team.
